{
  "text": "Working with natural extensions makes step (1) heavier in notation, and step (6) more complicated to implement. For example, instead of considering s, u-admissible curves, we employ the notion of \"staying in windows\" to define s, u-admissible sets, see section 2.5. The notion of \"staying in windows\", originally defined in [CITATION_1] , allows to prove that s, u-admissible sets satisfy the necessary abstract requirements to apply the refinement and prove step (6).",
